From kenton yee Subject proposed catcher re sub rule A lot of teams carry catchers on their man roster but the catcher is seldom ever He is only insurance in case of extra innings or the catcher is injured during a So to free up this roster spot for an extra pinch hitter or reliever why not invoke a catcher re substitution rule If the last roster catcher on a team is injured during a game the team is permitted to substitute in his place for defensive purposes a catcher who has previously been yanked from the Given this rule a team wouldn't need roster The catcher could be playing in AAA or be a non roster bullpen Ken